article.headline: Texas-San Antonio 64, SE Louisiana 57
article.story: SAN ANTONIO -- Demarco Stepter scored 15 points as UTSA defeated Southeastern Louisiana, 64-57, in Southland Conference play on Saturday. UTSA (13-8, 3-5) held a 37-28 lead at the half. Southeastern Louisiana (13-9, 5-4) cut the lead down to just four points at 49-45 with 9:38 left to play. UTSA would go on a 6-0 run from there to push their lead to 55-45, the largest of the game, and would not be threatened down the stretch. Terry Fields had 14 points, six rebounds, and four assists for the Roadrunners. The Lions were led by Patrick Sullivan's game-high 19 points. Jason Marks added 13 points. The Lions struggled from long range making just 2 of 17 (11.8 percent) from 3. The Roadrunners made 7 of 15 (46.7 percent) from 3. This snaps a three-game winning streak for the Lions and ends the Roadrunners five-game losing streak.
